(1164, 1757, 'kc_raw_content', '[kc_row use_container=\"yes\" _id=\"339038\"][kc_column width=\"12/12\" video_mute=\"no\" _id=\"489757\"][kc_row_inner column_align=\"middle\" video_mute=\"no\" _id=\"333159\"][kc_column_inner width=\"35.4%\" _id=\"369160\"][kc_spacing height=\"61px\" _id=\"35458\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"728728\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1758\"][kc_af_title heading=\"3\" align=\"center\" _id=\"301766\" title=\"Professor A.T AKINWALE\" subtitle=\"Dean, COLPHYS\"][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"64.59%\" _id=\"647301\"][kc_spacing height=\"61px\" _id=\"242866\"][kc_af_title heading=\"3\" align=\"center\" _id=\"845334\" title=\"Welcome to College Of Physical Science (COLPHYS)\"][kc_column_text _id=\"412373\"]<p>The College of Physical Sciences (COLPHYS) is one of the two Colleges created out of the defunct College of Natural Sciences (COLNAS) in 2014.Presently, the Departments in the College run four years Bachelor of Sciences Degree Programmes which are fully accredited by National Universities Commission (NUC).The Departments are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Department of Chemistry</li>\r\n<li>Department of Computer Science</li>\r\n<li>Department of Mathematics</li>\r\n<li>Department of Physics</li>\r\n<li>Department of Statistics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In addition to running degree programmes in these disciplines, the College provides teaching and laboratory services to students in other disciplines of the University at the 100 and 200 levels. The College is therefore foundational and central to effective running of academic programmes of the University</p>\r\n[/kc_column_text][kc_spacing height=\"12px\" _id=\"775583\"][/kc_column_inner][/kc_row_inner][kc_spacing height=\"42px\" _id=\"223119\"][/kc_column][/kc_row][kc_row use_container=\"yes\" _id=\"775575\"][kc_column width=\"12/12\" video_mute=\"no\" _id=\"702340\"][kc_call_to_action layout=\"2\" title=\"Meet Your HOD:apos:s\" desc=\"V2UgYXJlIGJsZXNzZWQgd2l0aCBudW1lcm